Ad Text:
We are seeking a highly skilled SAS solution designer to drive the successful delivery of technical solutions. The ideal candidate will be responsible for handling business requirements, impact analysis, effort estimation, solution design, governance activities, and technical documentation.



Key Responsibilities:
Collaborate with Credit Risk Business Stakeholders, Service Owners, Solution Engineers, and Line of Business (LOB) Leads to prioritize, size, and assess requirements and backlog.
Work closely with business units to understand Credit Risk-related data elements, including reference data, metadata, and data lineage.
Guide Agile teams in designing, developing, testing, implementing, and supporting technical solutions using full-stack development tools, technologies, and DevOps processes.
Translate business requirements into IT solution concepts and designs.
Develop solution architectures that ensure successful implementation while aligning with design principles and standards.
Conduct root cause analysis for production incidents, identify design defects or requirement gaps, and provide effective solutions.
Provide third-line support for technical issues where necessary.
Contribute to high-level IT & Business Solution Design documents.
Advise the business on the effective application of technologies.
Support end-to-end implementation planning.
Oversee and validate proposed complex changes to business services to ensure ongoing stability and sustainability.
Deliver cost estimates for design and development phases in collaboration with architects, business analysts, project managers, subject matter experts, and solution providers.
Assist Solution Engineers and Data Engineers in design and development.
Contribute to strategic design, development, and deployment supporting projects and deliverables.
Required Professional and Technical Expertise:
3+ years of experience as a SAS Tech Lead / Senior Developer in a similar role.
5+ years of experience in projects or delivering business and technology solutions involving complex data engineering processes.
5+ years of Advanced SQL and SAS experience, particularly in data manipulation and cleansing using Base SAS, SAS/Macro, SAS DI Studio, SAS Enterprise Guide, SAS Management Console, and overall SAS Platform.
Experience in Big Data technologies (Hadoop, Spark, Hive, HBase, Python) is a plus.
Experience in API Development (Java Spring, MVC) and Azure Cloud (Synapse Analytics, CosmosDB) is advantageous.
Knowledge of data warehousing, modeling, and integration tools such as Informatica, Sterling, and business intelligence tools like Power BI, Tableau.
Experience designing solutions within SAS 9.4 or Viya platform.
Hands-on experience in Azure cloud environments.

As the National Manager - Finance Business Partner based in Canberra, you will be responsible for guiding the organisation's financial planning, budgeting, forecasting, and performance analysis.

You will provide expert financial insights to senior leaders, ensuring alignment between financial outcomes and organisational priorities, while driving strong governance and supporting informed, data-driven decision-making across the business.

Details about the Client

ADF Careers is the largest workforce outsourcing solution in the southern hemisphere with over 80,000 applications received on average each year.
ADF Careers is on a mission to recruit the right people, in the right numbers, at the right time to support the Australian Defence Force to build, sustain and maximise Defence capability.


Our people are our greatest asset. We recognise and respect our people's need to work in ways that support their careers, families, and lifestyle. That's why we offer flexible working arrangements, learning pathways, additional leave entitlements and extensive corporate discounts across a variety of product and services. We want our people to be financially rewarded; to feel good and to go beyond what they thought possible at work.

Be you, and we'll be better together.

To find out more about our great employee benefits and what it's like to be part of the team, reach out to our friendly talent acquisition team.

Job Description

The National Manager - Finance Business Partner is a strategic leadership role responsible for leading the organisation's financial planning, budgeting, forecasting, pricing and performance analysis team. This role works closely with senior leaders and provides strategic insight and analytical leadership to inform decision-making strengthen financial governance and drive business performance. Based at our Headquarters in Canberra, this role is the first point of contact for all Finance Business Partner matters, providing expert advice to our Senior Leadership Team and supporting the Head of Finance to ensure alignment between financial outcomes and organisational priorities.

You will:

Partner with business leaders and support the development of annual budgets, rolling forecasts and scenario modelling aligned with business plans
Partner with Head of Functions and National Managers to interpret financial results and translate into actional insights for operational and strategic improvement
Provide strategic financial advice to the DFR Executive Leadership team and senior stakeholder
Identify financial levers, risks, opportunities and emerging trends to inform organisational strategy and priorities
Liaise directly with Commonwealth representatives with regards to financial queries and requests relating to DFR
Develop and maintain pricing models and strategies to ensure competitive positioning, profitability and compliance with Adecco DFR objectives.
Oversee monthly management reporting, variance analysis and executive-level committee financial insights and ensure integrity and timeliness of all reporting to internal and external stakeholders
Partner with the Finance Leadership Team to provide aligned, consistent and effective people capability services for Adecco DFR
Continuously improve Finance Business Partnering processes and offerings to support the Adecco DFR organisation.
Lead and develop a high performing team of Financial Analysts to deliver high-quality analysis, advice and service
Build financial literacy and accountability across DFR functions
Act as deputy to the Head of Finance, representing the finance function in internal and external forums as required
Maintain industry knowledge and appropriate accreditation to ensure exceptional level of support to the business.
Develop, manage and maintain a high service level client relationship through the provision of services that meet or exceed the expectations of Defence and the DFR Adecco contract, further encouraging a strong and ongoing relationship between Adecco and the Commonwealth of Australia.

Candidate's Profile

If you have worked in a similar position or just looking for your next opportunity that will make an impact, we want to speak with you.

Your background will demonstrate:

Extensive experience leading FP&A and/or finance business partnering functions in a complex or large-scale organisations
Demonstrated ability to provide strategic financial leadership and influence senior stakeholders
Strong people leadership and coaching capability
Significant analytical skillset, including the utilisation of BI and reporting tools
High-level communication, influencing, and stakeholder engagement skills.
Resilient and adaptable mindset, with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced and everchanging environment.
Experience with enterprise-level financial systems and performance reporting tools e.g Microsoft Dynamics 365, PowerBI

To apply for this position, you must be an Australian citizen and have the ability to maintain an Australian AGSVA security clearance.

How to apply

If eligible, please submit your resume; applications are open to all qualified Australian citizens regardless of their background, identity, experiences and beliefs.

If you need assistance during our recruitment process, please email Victoria Emms at victoria.emms@adecco.com.au for a confidential conversation.

To apply for this position, please submit your application online through our designated platform. The deadline for applications is 11:30 PM (AEST) on Friday 19th December. It's important to note that applications will be reviewed and processed as they are received.

Job Title: General Manager - Client success & Research Transformation
Ad Text:
Endpoint IQ is a Brisbane-based SaaS company working with universities, research institutes, and health services across Australia, New Zealand, and overseas. Our platforms streamline the end‑to‑end research management pipeline, so researchers spend less time on admin and more time on impact.

We’re looking for a solutions‑focused, personable leader for our Client Success and Implementation team. We’re a medium‑sized, specialist team with low ego, a collaborative style, and close relationships with our clients. With the pace of change across higher education, this role is ideal for someone who wants to help shape the next generation of research management systems while staying connected to the sector.

You will:

Lead a multidisciplinary team of project managers and product specialists (~12FTE) delivering multiple concurrent implementations (10–24 month programmes)

Bring research management expertise to challenge "lift and shift" processes and design better ways of working for our clients

Own our implementation framework and delivery standards across institutions in Australia and overseas

Ensure Level 2 application support and product-specialist knowledge flow cleanly through to our developers and support engineers

Support Sales with research-literate input to proposals and take part in pre-sales demos for new and upsell opportunities.

About you

You understand the research management ecosystem and how universities and health services actually get work done. You may have come up through a Research Office, Ethics and Governance, Grants, or Graduate Research, or you may have led delivery or support for research‑adjacent software. What matters most is practical experience helping researchers and professional staff navigate processes such as ethics review, grants and contracts, HDR candidature, or post‑award finance, and turning that understanding into reliable delivery, clear communication, and measurable outcomes.

You’ve worked across multiple stakeholder groups and are comfortable balancing day‑to‑day matters with the dynamics of multiple streams of project delivery. Whether your path has been operational within a research intensive organisation or product/delivery for a vendor you will bring credibility with research management professionals and the judgement to lead a team that’s close to clients and outcomes.

What you’ll bring

Meaningful experience in research management or a closely related domain, with fluency in processes like ethics/governance, grants and contracts, HDR/GR, or post‑award.

A track record delivering or supporting business systems, ideally SaaS.

Strength in stakeholder engagement across academic, professional, and IT groups, with clear, plain‑language communication.

Comfort moving between detail and big picture: from root‑cause analysis and SOPs to roadmap, prioritisation, and acceptance.

Team leadership that’s low‑ego, collaborative, and oriented to service quality and measurable client outcomes.

Why join Endpoint IQ

Stay adjacent to higher education and research while broadening into the tech sector

Work with multiple large orgnisations and see your ideas postitively influence practice across the sector

Join a supportive, close-knit team where your voice matters and bureaucracy is light

Work based in Toowong, with practical flexibility and occasional travel to clients and overseas conferences

Real opportunity to shape how research is managed during a time of major change in the sector.

Together building prosperity in the Kimberley and beyond — Safety, Sustainability, Community: it’s in our DNA.
 
At KMS, success is not just what we do — it’s how we do it. We’re seeking a hands on, outcomes focused Principal Continuous Improvement to embed a culture of improvement and lift performance across the business. You’ll be a trusted advisor to senior leaders and own enterprise level programs that strengthen governance, sustainability and stakeholder confidence.
 
About the Project

Kimberley Mineral Sands Pty Ltd (KMS) is a 50/50 joint venture between Sheffield Resources Limited and YGH Australia Investment Pty Ltd (Yansteel). The Thunderbird Mineral Sands Operation (Thunderbird) is located mid-way between Derby and Broome, in the Kimberley region of Western Australia. 

Thunderbird is one of the largest and highest-grade zircon mineral sands deposits in the world and contains valuable heavy minerals including ilmenite, zircon, leucoxene, and rutile, which are extracted and exported via the Port of Broome. 

Our head office is based in Broome, and together we are focused on delivering economic and social benefits for the West Kimberley and its communities. We do this through living our values of Integrity, Accountability, Humility, Co-Creation and Inclusivity. 



About the Role

Location: Perth or Broome (Monday–Friday corporate roster) with regular travel to the Thunderbird site
Department: Commercial & Finance
Reports to: Head of Commercial
 

What you’ll lead

Enterprise Continuous Improvement (CI) framework: design, implement and monitor a practical improvement framework aligned to organisational strategy; track outcomes and benefits with clear reporting.
Stewardship (organisational “wiring”) Program: own the design, governance and activities cadence (balanced scorecards, dashboards, KPIs) to drive accountability, transparency and responsible resource management.
Priority improvement delivery: identify and prioritise opportunities; facilitate CI activities such as value stream mapping, problem solving and idea generation; lead compliant process enhancements and sustainment plans.
Culture & capability: coach and mentor leaders and teams in CI methods (Lean, Six Sigma); develop tools, templates and training that build capability.
HS&E and risk alignment: ensure initiatives align with policies, risk frameworks, compliance requirements and our zero harm expectations.


About You
Degree in Business, Management or related discipline.
8+ years’ experience in continuous improvement, process optimisation or organisational development in complex environments.
Certification in Lean/Six Sigma or equivalent experience.
Strong analytics with the ability to translate data into actionable insights.
Highly effective stakeholder engagement and communication; you build trust quickly and collaborate to deliver meaningful change.
Leadership qualities that fit our environment: resilience and adaptability, a practical problem solving mindset, persistence and strong emotional intelligence.

Why join KMS?

Impact at enterprise scale: shape systems that improve performance and stewardship across the business.
Exposure & trust: partner closely with senior leaders; your advice and delivery will be visible and valued.
Community & purpose: contribute to prosperity in the Kimberley and beyond, grounded in safety and sustainability

Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion

KMS is committed to advancing an inclusive and diverse workforce culture and environment where people feel comfortable to be themselves. We acknowledge the different skills, experiences, and perspectives that people from diverse backgrounds including, race, ethnicity, disability, age, gender identity and sexual orientation bring to the workplace, will only strengthen our workforce.

We strongly encourage applications from our key priority communities – Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, women, youth, and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.  

How to Apply

Please submit your application via seek, or the KMS Careers Portal. If you have questions, contact Recruitment at recruitment@kmsands.com.au. Applications are reviewed as they are received and the advert may be removed should we find a suitable applicant.

Ad Text:
Lee Family Office is a privately held investment group with a diverse portfolio across agriculture, forestry, private credit, real estate, and alternative assets. As we continue to expand, we are seeking a Senior Investment Analyst to work closely with the CEO, Chief Investment Officer (CIO), and senior leadership team on high-impact investment strategy and execution.

This is a broad, hands-on role offering exposure to the full investment lifecycle — origination, modelling, diligence, execution, and portfolio management — across multiple sectors and jurisdictions. The right candidate will thrive in a fast-paced environment, enjoy taking ownership, and be motivated by meaningful responsibility and direct access to decision-makers.

You’ll also have the opportunity to travel domestically and internationally for site inspections, meetings, and due-diligence work.

Key Responsibilities

Lead research and sector analysis across agriculture, forestry, private credit, real estate, and alternative investments.

Build, maintain, and stress-test sophisticated financial models for acquisitions, capital projects, structured lending, and portfolio scenarios.

Produce high-quality investment papers, valuation reports, and recommendations for CEO/CIO review.

Support end-to-end transaction processes: due diligence, term-sheet development, financial analysis, structuring, and completion.

Monitor the performance of existing investments; prepare monthly and quarterly reporting; identify risks, trends, and optimisation opportunities.

Liaise with a broad network of external advisors including legal, valuation, banking, and technical specialists.

Provide analytical and commercial support to subsidiaries and group businesses, including forecasting and project evaluation.

Uphold rigorous financial controls, risk processes, and regulatory compliance.

Contribute proactively to strategic initiatives and special projects led by the CEO and CIO.

About You

Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Economics, Commerce, or similar; CFA, CA, or CPA highly regarded.

3–7+ years’ experience in investment banking, private equity, corporate finance, or funds management.

Advanced financial modelling, valuation, and analytical capability.

Exceptional written communication and presentation skills.

Strong commercial judgement with an eye for detail and accuracy.

Comfortable working across multiple projects and deadlines with autonomy.

Professional, discreet, and confident engaging with senior executives and external stakeholders.

Willingness to travel domestically and internationally when required.

Why Join Us

This is a rare opportunity to join a dynamic family office where high performance is recognised and your work has direct influence on portfolio decisions and long-term strategy. You will gain broad asset-class exposure, close mentorship from senior leaders, and the chance to contribute meaningfully to the growth of a multi-generational investment group.

Reporting Platform Analyst / Engineer


Location: Melbourne, Brisbane or Sydney (Hybrid)
Type: 3-month contract (potential to extend)
Start Date: Ideally available to start next week

Applicants must have Australian PR or Citizenship.

Monitor regulatory and employment law changes and ensure compliance (eg WGEA reporting).

Advise HR and hiring managers on remuneration queries, job evaluation, grading and benchmark activities.

Ensure timely processing of remuneration related invoices and transactions.




About you




Experience in compensation & benefits or reward/people analytics.

Advanced Excel and HRIS skills, strong attention to detail and stakeholder communication.

Knowledge of Australian remuneration regulations and benchmarking best practice.

This is a country focused role with global and regional team connections, requiring occasional flexibility in working hours.

Be part of a transformative journey with a supportive, collaborative team across the APAC region. Sydney / Brisbane based candidates are strongly preferred.

Job Title: LCS Business Strategy and Operations Senior Associate, GTM
Ad Text:
At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google’s technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan for more information.

Minimum qualifications:

Bachelor's degree or equivalent practical experience.
4 years of experience in management consulting, sales operations, business strategy, investment banking, venture capital, private equity, or corporate advisory, or 2 years of experience with an advanced degree.
Preferred qualifications:

Experience using Business Intelligence (BI) and dashboards, and analyzing large data sets.
Ability to work and succeed in a fluid and an ambiguous environment.
Excellent collaboration skills, and ability to work with people from a range of backgrounds and experience.
Excellent communication, teamwork, and presentation skills.
Strong focus on execution and getting things done, balancing quality with speed.
About the job


The Go-to-Market (GTM) team is the trusted sounding board for the Australia New Zealand leadership team. We are a team who can solve complex problems and bring strategies to life while ensuring that the business runs flawlessly. We help shape the future through go-to-market strategy, power the business through seamless operational excellence and grow leaders. Team members are strategic and analytical, with the ability to execute quickly and get things done.

As a Strategy and Operations Senior Associate, you will provide business critical insights and recommendations that support decision making, cross-functional alignment of goals and expectations, and drive/help teams to execute plans and operate.

In this role, you will respond to problem statements raised by the local leadership team via hypothesis generation, analyzing information, assessing potential options, and putting forward recommendations.

You will help to set the focus, pace, and direction of our business across AUNZ Large Customer Sales and unite teams to deliver on Google’s most important business opportunities by supporting, challenging, and enabling our sales organization.

Responsibilities

Draw interpretable insights from sophisticated business analyses and advanced modeling.
Design processes, tools, and operating cadences to achieve organizational outcomes.
Develop comprehensive sales, product or business strategies that solve complex business challenges and address the needs of customers and stakeholders across various functions to drive incremental growth.
Communicate data-driven recommendations to leadership and to the broader organization in structured presentations, identifying key takeaways.
Define actionable plans and roadmaps and align cross-functional stakeholders to drive successful implementation of change initiatives.
